{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "LocalScaleMeteorology",
        "description": "Local-scale boundary-layer meteorology from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) \"Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics\", 2nd ed., Chapter 16 \"Meteorology of the Local Scale\". A flat observed-only algebraic component that combines atmospheric static-stability analysis, Monin-Obukhov surface-layer similarity theory and Pasquill stability-class estimation: from the air temperature and pressure, the surface-layer geometry, the friction velocity u_star and the surface sensible heat flux q_z it computes the potential temperature θ (Eq. 16.14), the actual and potential-temperature lapse rates dT_dz and dθ_dz (Eqs. 16.16-16.18), the Monin-Obukhov length L and its inverse L_inv (Eq. 16.70), the stability parameter ζ = z/L, the Businger-Dyer stability functions φ_m, φ_h and their integrated forms ψ_m, ψ_h (Eqs. 16.75, 16.78-16.79), the stability-corrected mean wind speed ū (Eq. 16.66) and the Pasquill stability class (1=A to 6=F) via the Golder (1972) correlation (Eq. 16.83). Twelve purely-algebraic equations, no time integration. Migrated from AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391 src/local_scale_meteorology.jl:234 (`LocalScaleMeteorology` @component).",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_dynamics",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "boundary-layer",
            "monin-obukhov",
            "potential-temperature",
            "pasquill",
            "observed-only",
            "ch16"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDynamics.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-81lv)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed. Wiley. Chapter 16 (Meteorology of the Local Scale), pp. 720-760 -- Eq. 16.8 (dry adiabatic lapse rate), Eq. 16.14 (potential temperature), Eqs. 16.16-16.18 (static stability), Eq. 16.66 (logarithmic wind profile), Eq. 16.70 (Monin-Obukhov length), Eq. 16.75 (Businger-Dyer stability functions), Eqs. 16.78-16.79 (integrated stability functions), Eq. 16.83 (Golder correlation for Pasquill classes). ISBN 978-0-471-72018-8."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Businger, J. A., Wyngaard, J. C., Izumi, Y., & Bradley, E. F. (1971). Flux-Profile Relationships in the Atmospheric Surface Layer. Journal of the Atmospheric Sciences, 28(2), 181-189. DOI 10.1175/1520-0469(1971)028<0181:FPRITA>2.0.CO;2."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Golder, D. (1972). Relations among stability parameters in the surface layer. Boundary-Layer Meteorology, 3(1), 47-58. DOI 10.1007/BF00769106."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "LocalScaleMeteorology": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc3918e1eef2c2ee6d8fa8dd73c8f13a85a47:src/local_scale_meteorology.jl:234\n\nUpstream `LocalScaleMeteorology` is a ModelingToolkit `@component` that combines the atmospheric static-stability diagnostics of the sibling `AtmosphericStability` component and the Monin-Obukhov surface-layer similarity theory of `SurfaceLayerProfile` with a Pasquill stability-class estimate, all from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 16 (Meteorology of the Local Scale, pp. 720-760). It declares 18 referenced `@constants`, 10 `@parameters`, 12 `@variables` and 12 equations, returning `System(eqs, t; name)`.\n\nFlat single model -- NOT a coupling.couple composition. docs/migration-tracker.md tags this row `features: variables, parameters, coupling.couple` with `depends_on: AtmosphericStability, SurfaceLayerProfile`, and the upstream docstring calls it a \"composite system\". The upstream code, however, builds a plain `System(eqs, t; name)` with all 12 equations written inline (src/local_scale_meteorology.jl:308-374): it does NOT call `System(...; systems=[...])` and constructs no subcomponents -- it re-implements the AtmosphericStability and SurfaceLayerProfile physics directly. The migration therefore represents it as a single flat model with a 12-equation block, not as an ESS subsystem-composed model; the tracker `depends_on` entries record conceptual provenance (the sibling components whose physics is reused), not a structural dependency. The shared equations are byte-identical to the corresponding equations of the gate-verified sibling migrations stability.esm and surface_layer_profile.esm.\n\nSystem kind: all 12 equations are explicit algebraic assignments (lhs ~ rhs) with no `D(.)` operator -- every output is a closed-form expression of the inputs. `system_kind` is left unset (default 'ode'); the compiled system has zero differential states, exactly as for the siblings stability.esm and surface_layer_profile.esm.\n\nVariable classification. (1) T, T_below, p, z, z₀, Δz, T₀, ρ, u_star, q_z: upstream MTK `@parameters` -- the external inputs -- encoded type: parameter with their upstream defaults. (2) θ, dT_dz, dθ_dz, L, ζ, φ_m, φ_h, ψ_m, ψ_h, ū, L_inv, pasquill_class: upstream `@variables`, each the LHS of exactly one purely-algebraic equation -- observed algebraic outputs with no time derivative and hence no initial condition -- encoded type: state with no default. (3) g, κ, ĉ_p, R_air, p₀, Γ_d, ε_q, z₀_ref and the 10 Golder coefficients: upstream MTK `@constants`; the ESS schema has no `constant` variable type, so each is encoded type: parameter carrying its upstream value as default, exactly as in stability.esm and surface_layer_profile.esm.\n\nOmitted constants a_D, b_D. Upstream declares 12 Golder (1972) coefficient `@constants` a_A, b_A, ..., a_F, b_F (src lines 251-262). The pasquill_class equation (src lines 358-373) is a 5-level nested `ifelse`; its fourth branch -- the class-D / neutral boundary -- is compared against the class-E coefficients a_E + b_E*log10(z₀/z₀_ref) (src line 365), so a_D and b_D (both declared 0.0) appear in no equation. An unreferenced MTK `@constant` is not collected into the built `System` (the same reason g is omitted from stability.esm), so a_D and b_D are omitted here; the remaining 10 Golder coefficients are all referenced and retained. The upstream `LocalScaleMeteorology structure` testitem checks only `length(equations(sys)) == 12` and a handful of named parameters, consistent with this.\n\nκ_exp local. Upstream binds a plain Julia local `κ_exp = R_air / ĉ_p` (~ 0.286, the Poisson exponent R/c_p) and uses it as the exponent of the potential-temperature equation (Eq. 16.14). MTK inlines it when `System(eqs, t)` is built; the .esm mirrors this, writing equation 1's exponent as the sub-expression R_air / ĉ_p.\n\nEquation faithfulness. The 12 upstream equations (src lines 308-374) are preserved in upstream order: θ (Eq. 16.14), dT_dz (finite-difference actual lapse rate), dθ_dz (Eqs. 16.16-16.18), L (Eq. 16.70), L_inv = 1/L, ζ = z/L, φ_m and φ_h (Eq. 16.75 Businger-Dyer), ψ_m and ψ_h (Eqs. 16.78-16.79), ū (Eq. 16.66 with the Eq. 16.77 correction), and pasquill_class (Eq. 16.83 Golder correlation). The L, ζ, φ_m, φ_h, ψ_m, ψ_h and ū equation trees are copied verbatim from the sibling surface_layer_profile.esm, where `mtk2esm` reordered the commutative */+ operands of L, rewrote x^(-n) as 1/x^n in φ_m/φ_h, folded ((1-15ζ)^0.25)^2 to (1-15ζ)^0.5 in ψ_m/ψ_h, and folded the π/2 term of ψ_m to the float literal 1.5707963267948966. The θ, dT_dz and dθ_dz trees match the corresponding stability.esm equations.\n\nIdentifiers. Upstream Unicode identifiers are kept verbatim (θ, dθ_dz, Γ_d, p₀, Δz, ĉ_p, κ, ε_q, z₀, z₀_ref, T₀, ρ, ζ, φ_m, φ_h, ψ_m, ψ_h, ū), matching surface_layer_profile.esm. R_air is the dry-air specific gas constant in J/(kg*K); it is named R_air rather than the schema-reserved bare name R, correct since it is dimensionally J/(kg*K), not the universal gas constant in J/(mol*K).\n\nUnits are SI-coherent and carried verbatim from the upstream declarations; they are descriptive metadata (the ESS runners perform no dimensional analysis).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1.0e-6). The system is a closed-form algebraic evaluation -- no ODE integration, no implicit solve -- so there is no integrator error to bound; rel=1.0e-6 covers float64 round-off and cross-runner libm differences in the ^/log/log10/atan chain, matching the siblings. Near-zero outputs in the neutral regime -- ζ, L_inv, ψ_m, ψ_h ~ 1e-12..1e-14 at the default q_z = 0, where the ε_q heat-flux regularization makes |L| enormous -- carry a per-assertion abs=1.0e-6; the exact-zero actual lapse rate dT_dz (T = T_below) carries abs=1.0e-12.\n\nTest reproduction. The 10 inline tests reproduce every LocalScaleMeteorology scenario of test/local_scale_meteorology_test.jl plus the AtmosphericDynamics.jl docs \"Complete Boundary Layer Analysis\" example: `defaults_baseline` exercises all 12 outputs at the declared defaults (the upstream `LocalScaleMeteorology structure` testitem); `potential_temp_850hPa` and `potential_temp_cold_low_pressure` reproduce the `Potential temperature` and `Physical constraints` θ checks; `pasquill_unstable_class_C` and `pasquill_stable_class_F` reproduce the two `Pasquill stability classification` testitems (the upstream <= 3 / >= 4 assertions become the exact classes 3 and 6); `physical_constraints_wind_class_D` reproduces the `Physical constraints` ū > 0 check. The added scenarios `light_wind_strong_heating_class_A`, `moderately_unstable_class_B` and `inversion_stable_class_E` extend Pasquill coverage to classes 1, 2 and 5 (the suite spans the full A-F range) and exercise the inversion (dT_dz > 0) and stable-branch (ζ > 0) cases; `summer_afternoon_boundary_layer` reproduces the docs composite example. Expected values are the float64 results of the upstream formulas; the L/ζ/φ/ψ/ū values of the default and summer-afternoon scenarios agree with the corresponding surface_layer_profile.esm tests, as those equations are shared verbatim.\n\nExamples. The 3 examples reproduce AtmosphericDynamics.jl docs figures (docs/src/local_scale_meteorology.md): `potential_temperature_profile` sweeps pressure p (the `Potential Temperature Profile` figure); `monin_obukhov_length_vs_heat_flux` sweeps the surface heat flux q_z over the unstable regime (the `Monin-Obukhov Length vs Heat Flux` figure); `pasquill_class_vs_roughness_length` sweeps the roughness length z₀ at a fixed unstable heat flux to trace the discrete Pasquill A-F classification against the Golder (1972) z₀ correlation (the `Monin-Obukhov Length vs Roughness Length for Pasquill Stability Classes` figure), the diagnostic distinctive to this composite component. All three example sweeps stay in the unstable / neutral regime (ζ <= 0); the example renderer eagerly evaluates both `ifelse` branches, and the Businger-Dyer unstable branch (1-15ζ)^(-1/4) is real-valued only for ζ <= 0."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-06
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 288.15,
                    "description": "Air temperature at height z"
                },
                "T_below": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 288.15,
                    "description": "Air temperature at height z - Δz"
                },
                "p": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 101325.0,
                    "description": "Pressure at height z"
                },
                "z": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 10.0,
                    "description": "Height above ground"
                },
                "z₀": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.1,
                    "description": "Roughness length (Table 16.1)"
                },
                "Δz": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Vertical spacing for gradient calculation"
                },
                "T₀": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 288.15,
                    "description": "Reference temperature (surface)"
                },
                "ρ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^3",
                    "default": 1.225,
                    "description": "Air density"
                },
                "u_star": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.3,
                    "description": "Friction velocity"
                },
                "q_z": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Surface sensible heat flux (positive upward)"
                },
                "g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s^2",
                    "default": 9.807,
                    "description": "Gravitational acceleration"
                },
                "κ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "von Karman constant (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ĉ_p": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(kg*K)",
                    "default": 1005.0,
                    "description": "Specific heat of air at constant pressure"
                },
                "R_air": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(kg*K)",
                    "default": 287.0,
                    "description": "Gas constant for dry air"
                },
                "p₀": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 101325.0,
                    "description": "Reference pressure (sea level)"
                },
                "Γ_d": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K/m",
                    "default": 0.00976,
                    "description": "Dry adiabatic lapse rate (Eq. 16.8: g/c_p = 9.807/1005 ≈ 9.76 K/km)"
                },
                "ε_q": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 1e-10,
                    "description": "Small regularization for heat flux"
                },
                "z₀_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference length for dimensionless log"
                },
                "a_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": -0.096,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient a for Pasquill class A (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "b_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.029,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient b for Pasquill class A (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "a_B": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": -0.037,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient a for Pasquill class B (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "b_B": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.029,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient b for Pasquill class B (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "a_C": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": -0.002,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient a for Pasquill class C (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "b_C": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.018,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient b for Pasquill class C (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "a_E": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.004,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient a for Pasquill class E (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "b_E": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": -0.018,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient b for Pasquill class E (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "a_F": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.035,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient a for Pasquill class F (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "b_F": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": -0.036,
                    "description": "Golder (1972) coefficient b for Pasquill class F (Eq. 16.83: 1/L = a + b·log₁₀(z₀))"
                },
                "θ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "K",
                    "description": "Potential temperature (Eq. 16.14)"
                },
                "dT_dz": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "K/m",
                    "description": "Actual temperature lapse rate"
                },
                "dθ_dz": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "K/m",
                    "description": "Potential temperature gradient"
                },
                "L": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Monin-Obukhov length (Eq. 16.70)"
                },
                "ζ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Stability parameter z/L (dimensionless)"
                },
                "φ_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Momentum stability function (Eq. 16.75) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "φ_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat stability function (Eq. 16.75) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ψ_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Integrated momentum stability function (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ψ_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Integrated heat stability function (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ū": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Mean wind speed at height z (Eq. 16.66)"
                },
                "L_inv": {
                    "type": "state",
