                    "description": "Unstable surface layer — reproduces the first `Pasquill stability classification` testitem (u_star = 0.5 m/s, q_z = 300 W/m^2, z₀ = 0.1 m, T₀ = 300 K, ρ = 1.225 kg/m^3). The Monin-Obukhov length L ≈ -39.2 m is negative (the upstream `L < 0` assertion) and the Pasquill class is 3 (C, slightly unstable) — the upstream test asserts `pasquill_class ≤ 3`. ζ < 0 selects the Businger-Dyer unstable branch of φ_m and ψ_m.",
