                {
                    "id": "physical_constraints_wind_class_D",
                    "description": "Physical constraints — reproduces the second `Physical constraints` testitem (u_star = 0.5 m/s, z = 10 m, z₀ = 0.1 m, q_z = 50 W/m^2, T₀ = 288.15 K, ρ = 1.225 kg/m^3): the mean wind speed ū ≈ 5.58 m/s is positive. The weak heat flux gives a large-magnitude L ≈ -226 m, so L_inv ≈ -0.0044 m^-1 places the atmosphere in Pasquill class 4 (D, near-neutral). The unstable-branch stability functions φ_m and φ_h are positive (the upstream `Physical constraints` φ > 0 check).",
