                {
                    "id": "inversion_stable_class_E",
                    "description": "Surface temperature inversion with surface cooling (T = 290.15 K above T_below = 288.15 K over Δz = 100 m, u_star = 0.25 m/s, q_z = -60 W/m^2). Temperature increasing with height gives a positive actual lapse rate dT_dz = 0.02 K/m and a strongly positive potential-temperature gradient dθ_dz = 0.02976 K/m (stable stratification). The downward heat flux gives a positive Monin-Obukhov length L ≈ 23.6 m, so ζ > 0 selects the stable branch where φ_m = φ_h = 1 + 4.7ζ and ψ_m = ψ_h = -4.7ζ; L_inv ≈ 0.042 m^-1 gives Pasquill class 5 (E, slightly stable).",
