                {
                    "id": "summer_afternoon_boundary_layer",
                    "description": "Summer-afternoon boundary layer from the AtmosphericDynamics.jl docs \"Complete Boundary Layer Analysis\" example (T = 298.15 K at 10 m, T_below = 300.15 K at the surface — superadiabatic, p = 100000 Pa, z = 10 m, z₀ = 0.1 m, Δz = 10 m, T₀ = 300.15 K, ρ = 1.18 kg/m^3, u_star = 0.35 m/s, q_z = 150 W/m^2). A strongly unstable surface layer: θ ≈ 299.3 K, dθ_dz ≈ -0.190 K/m (unstable), L ≈ -25.9 m, ζ ≈ -0.386, ū ≈ 3.45 m/s, Pasquill class 3 (C). Touches all 12 outputs; the L/ζ/φ/ψ/ū values agree with the surface_layer_profile.esm summer_afternoon_boundary_layer test (shared equations).",
